FBIS4-36424 "drnes111_j_94028" FBIS-NES-94-111 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Two Northern Aircraft Said Shot Down Over Aden Two Northern Aircraft Said Shot Down Over Aden NC0906103894 Paris AFP in English 1016 GMT 9 Jun 94 NC0906103894 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 9 (AFP) -- Two northern warplanes were shot down on Thursday [9 June] as they bombed Aden airport in south Yemen, witnesses said. Four planes bombed the airport area, but one slammed into the sea and a second crashed into the city's residential Shaykh 'Usman district after running into anti-aircraft fire, they said. Northern warplanes launched a second raid half an hour later. There were no immediate details of casualties. Southern warplanes based at the airport have taken part in bombing runs to try to stop the northern advance on Aden which was declared the capital of an independent state last month.
